creditline: Gift of Elizabeth, Julie, and Catherine Andrus in memory of John and Marion Andrus
inscription:
Signature, Date, Inscription, Stamps

inscribed in plate at top: [LEONIS SUFFOCATI EXVVIIS INDVITVR HERCVLES]

inscribed on verso in graphite: VGUX [code for Prouté, Paris]
markings: red stamp on verso, upper left: Josef V. Novák (L.1949)
provenance: Josef V. Novák, sale 1904; Paul Prouté, Paris; John E. Andrus III, Wayzata, Minn.; by descent to his daughters, Elizabeth, Katie, and Julie. Earlier provenances have been gathered, but further research will increase our knowledge of their histories.
signed: monogram and date in plate at lower left: [1548 / HSB]
title: Hercules Killing the Nemean Lion, From the Labors of Hercules
